  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate the efficacy and adverse events of intensity
      modulated radiation therapy (IMRT) concurrent with chemotherapy for anal squamous carcinoma.
      All enrolled anal squamous carcinoma patients are intented to receive IMRT concurrent with
      Capecitabine + mitomycin Â± cetuximab targeted therapy.
    </textblock>
